==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Irenics
<hw>I*ren"ics</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Eccl.)</fld>
<def>That branch of Christian science which treats of the methods of
securing unity among Christians or harmony and union among the churches;
-- called also <altname>Irenical theology</altname>.</def>
<rj><au>Schaff-Herzog.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Irestone</ent>⟦br⟧
